FT  04 MAR 92 / International Capital Markets: Skandia Finans to diversify
SKANDIA Finans, a wholly- owned subsidiary of Foersaekrings Skandia, the
Swedish insurance group, plans to expand its operations by opening a
brokerage house, AP-DJ reports from Stockholm.
The application for the new company, to be called Skandinavien
Fondkommission, was submitted yesterday to the government for approval.
Skandia Finans will be the sole owner and provide SKr52m of capital.
Mr Lars Lundquist, who was appointed president, said: 'We believe there is a
place for us on the market.' Institutional investors and big private
investors were seen as potential clients, he added.
